div.h1: PDE and PTE Entry Layout (4 bytes each)
div.p: 32-bit x86 Page Directory and Page Table Entry Structure

Translation:
PDE = PD[pd_index]
PTE = PT[pt_index] (where PT = PDE frame)
phys = PTE.frame + offset

ul.li: A: CPU sets on read (both PDE/PTE)
D: CPU sets on write (PTE only)
PTE: Dirty bit (set by CPU on write)
Often used for: COW, swap, etc.
